          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The gas target side was filled with 500 mbar of He gas.",
                "The scattering chamber, consisted of two sections-",
                "a vacuum side and a gas target side separated by",
                "a 1.98 mg/cm2 Ni window coated with a 100 mug/cm2 Au",
                "flash to prevent leaks."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two delta-E-E double sided silicon",
                "strip detector telescopes within the gas volume at 45",
                "degree on either side of the beam line were used to",
                "detect protons and reconstruct their trajectory back to",
                "a position of origin in the gas. Each telescope",
                "consisted of a 67 mum delta-E detector with 48*48",
                "strips and pitch 335 mum, a 470 mum E1 detector and a",
                " 464 mum E2 detector, each with 16*16 strips and pitch",
                " 3 mm, 5 and 6 cm behind the delta-E detector,",
                "respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The spectra must first be corrected for the change in",
                "efficiency with c.m. beam energy.",
                "Errors on the resonance energies and( hence 22Mg",
                "excitation energies) result from the angular straggling",
                "of protons through the gas and detectors, the error in",
                "the energy loss corrected proton energy and the finite",
                "pixel size and the error in the resonance energy",
                "resulting from the Lorentzian fitting."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The Radioactive Ion Beam facility at the University",
                "Catholique de Louvain in Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium was",
                "used to carry out the experimental work.",
                "Two 200 mm**2 face barrier detectors, at 170-degree on",
                "either side of the beam line, were used to detect",
                "elastically scattered 18Ne beam particles from a",
                " 200 mug/cm**2 Au foil. This allowed the beam to be",
                "normalized."
              ]
            }
          ],
